values: Okay, so here they are. They really don't do it justice. And it's bigger than it looks. I took them during and the completed tattoo one about an hour or two after, so it is raised and red, naturally.

i got my first tattoo today!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! @ Babylon Tattoo in Ft.Lauderdale, Rama did it and he is amazing! It's a swallow, medium sized, kind of big, on my right shoulder. It's in color and has stardusting around it. I'll probably take a picture and post it. My mom took two while he was doing it, I'll post those too. It didn't hurt as bad as I thought it did. At all. It felt like...a drill, kind of. I felt all of the vibrations. At some points, it sort of even felt good. It's hard to explain to someone who doesn't have one. When he was going over bone it wasn't the most pleasant, but not OMG I'M GOING TO CRY AND PASS OUT bad. I want more!! <3

i'm happy. this isn't the place for it, so i won't go into too much detail like i could, that's for my ana-log [did you catch the pun there?]. i haven't had anything to eat all day, and i feel great. i don't feel hungry. i just came back from walgreens, where i bought this thing called aquaban, it's a diuretic, and syrup of ipecac. also bought fat free slices of turkey breast, 2 bottles of fruit 2 o, which is flavored and has no calories. no sugar no carbs. but it does have sodium, so it's a bit worse than normal water. but the diuretic will take care of that. so tonight i'm planning on eating 4 slices of turkey breast [25 calories per slice, so that's 100 calories] and if we have any, a few baby carrots, like 4. only even numbers. always even numbers. can't be odd. carrots have, let me check my resources....okay, gross, nevermind. they have way too many calories in them. i mean, yes, i know they are supposed to be negative calorie food, but still, who really knows? better to be safe than sorry. but i guess it doesn't really matter if i eat them or not since i'll just be throwing them up anyway. i'm trying the syrup of ipecac tonight. god, i bet it tastes gross. but i look gross, so it's deserved, i guess. no pain, no gain. the thinner the winner. a moment on the lips, forever on the hips. nothing tastes as good as thin feels.

deleting journal entries, but you can't do that with real moments from your life.




didn't go to school today. not sick, just couldn't, spirit wasn't in it. 
damian isn't coming this weekend, either. i hope he can next weekend.

my first kiss at the public execution the blood brothers The carnival's glossy ghosts zebra-painted horses parade the cotton candy prostitutes caramel apple corpses singing: "Just this way to the neon orange gallows! Tonight we tie the noose around the killer's collar! Watch him play his wind pipe organ!" Just five dollars to see a face explode, to see a man strung up by his throat. Come one! Come all! If you look close enough you'll see death's machinery exposed. So won't you hold me closer just one more minute until the executions over? just one more minute Won't you behead another c'mon we're waiting won't you shock and entertain us? The hangman selling tickets to the sparkling death scene. Tonight we watch the rope choke a conscience clean. See it up close, see it in person! His lips spun like revolving fun house doors as the hush kisses at our neck nape. "Any final words for your loving audience?" says the man with the dazzling sapphire cape. So won't you hold me closer just one more minute until the executions over? just one more minute Won't you behead another c'mon we're waiting Won't you shock and entertain us? [x2] Until the end of the world? Snap, snap, snap goes the neck. "Rah, rah, rah!" the audience. Black, black, black goes his face. The sky spreads like thighs inside lace. [x2] so like every day.

if there were a year i would have a breakdown, i think this would be it. 
it's not that the material is too hard or anything. 
it's that i feel staggered. stifled. like i'm being crushed. 
sometimes.








this spring break the same group and teacher i went to france with two years ago is going to hungary, austria, germany, and the czech republic.
i'll probably go. my senior grad trip. my reward for this constant trying. anyways.

aromatherapy massage, anyone?

it is wonderful.

<big><big><big>ever so sweet</big></big></big>



damian came down again this weekend. =] it was...absolutely wonderful. he's absolutely wonderful. <3 i can't describe it, because nothing i could say would do it or him any kind of justice. 
we went shopping at the broward mall on saturday and damn, that boy can spend money. one word: suit. ______ lol
and when i left him, when i had to walk away while he was putting on his shoes from when they made him take them off for security, i cried. i did well when i physically, actually said goodbye to him, was hugging him and such [[ so not a proper goodbye ]], but then at that moment it was like: oh my god, i'm not going to see him again for two weeks at least, and this is the last time i'll see him, this is the closest i will get to him until then. he is only like twenty feet away from me, and i cannot touch him or talk to him.

now all i have are old pictures, songs, memories, and the smell of him on my pillow and the bled shirt. 

i miss him already.

okay. here's what i don't get. i now have to make sure i screen my comments of those who aren't listed as friends, since my immature ex boyfriend is fond of leaving some. to you: stop reading my journal, stop trying to comment, just leave me alone and move on with your life; don't make me a part of it. i am over you, i am happy now, so get the fuck away. =] thank you. you said you didn't want to know me, to have me in any way in your life, so then how come you find it necessary to read my journal and know what i'm doing? just go away. it's as over as it's ever going to be. i have too many things to concentrate on, and you're not one of them. on another note. school has gotten progressively better, and i think i am getting out of advanced aerobics. i still need a PE class, but it's strange....i'm getting a class, probably, that isn't real. well, when i know more about it, i'll update. nothing is laid in stone yet. ap euro is going to be tough. i can tell already. not because of the material--because of the teacher. i had mr mullin in tenth grade and he was hard then, too. i might switch ap environmental science next half of the year to exploratory teaching and be a teachers aid. that'd be fun. i don't need another ap.

Damian came down for the weekend and it was also the first time he met my parents. He slept at my house, and my parents really like him. It's not surprising, because he's wonderful and has impeccable manners, but it's very nice, very comforting. He was even allowed to sleep with me--not the first night, but the second night, and now every night after. My mother especially likes him-- and she told me that she feels something different about this guy, about this relationship. She said it could have something to do with the fact that he's twenty, living in Orlando, and has a well paying job; but I don't think so, and neither does she. It's him it has to do with and what we have, not any material facts about him. I can't believe my mom even recognizes it--of course I do, and I would expect her to, but not so early. This relationship is crazily perfect, crazily wonderful. He's probably coming down next weekend, too. If he can manage it with work, then he is. My mom and dad are paying for his flight down--55 minute flight beats a lonnnng greyhound bus ride. definitely. 

I can't believe I have school tomorrow. 
WOW.

weirrrrd. bad day. great night. --didn't talk to damian all day. ALL day. even started getting mad. but he came on at like idk 2 am and explained. all legitimate so it's all great. AND he is coming down here tomorrow till sunday. YESSSS. EDIT: ''tomorrow'' as in FRIDAY. it's late at night//early morning so i realized this entry is dated friday and he's not coming saturday. what a great way to start the school year. my parents will love him. he is SO nice. <3 my life is unfolding itself out perfectly. i am so happy.

I miss writing entries that I really mean. It's been so long since I've been able to do that, or was in the mood for it..& didn't want to offend people. nearly thinking of making this friends only, or at least making the comments friends only, because a certain loserexboyfriendwithnothingbettertodo has been leaving equally stupid comments. School is right around the corner. Things are so hectic, but then they're so lazy. If Damian is coming this weekend, I have a lot of cleaning to do,seeing as for some reason my dad wanted to pull apart my whole computer room. Weirrrd. I hope he's able to come though. What a wonderful way to start the school year. And it'd be so nice for my parents and him to finally get acquainted. Ahh...another school year. & after this one, I'll be 300 miles away in Orlando attending UCF. And I won't be living in a dorm. I have better arrangements. How many times have I said something like this about the future, though? That's something to think about. But it's oh-so-much more realistic now, because I've got so much school work this long distance relationship won't be so hard; it's only a year till it happens; i'm over dealing with immature boys who can't make up their minds. I have a good head on my shoulders; I know what I want. I'm finally thinking of that. & someone else is too. School.Damian.The Future. It's all I'm thinking of now. Nothing, no NOTHING, else. It's quite frightening. The lot of it. Well, it's late. I'm done staying up and waiting. Goodnight.

Today was really interesting. I got out of bed because I had to throw up. I'm really sick. I mean REALLY sick. I feel sad, because Sarah and Britney are complete bitches. They told everyone I have an STD, just because I slept with both of their boyfriends on Saturday night. I'm so sad. My kitten got run over this afternoon. I found him when I was coming home from school. His head was all squished. I took some photos. I'll miss him. Poor kitty. Last night I had to shave my entire body. Apparently, the lice that I caught from Amanda's friend are really hard to get rid of. I look quite strange with no hair and eyebrows. I'd post pictures, but my webcam is broken. I am sharpening my knives before I go to work today, because I'm going to cut out Robert's heart and feed it to him for losing my mail. I want to say thanks to simon and Abbey and Dave and the other Simon for helping me on Saturday. You guys are the best. By the way, if you happen to find my wallet, keys or underwear, could you SMS me? Adrian has my number. I went to the doctor yesterday, and he said I have a terrible skin disease which prevents me from coming into contact with other human beings. And bipolar disorder. That's enough for now. But I'll leave you with this poem I wrote. It's about my friend Robert, who has bipolar disorder. Just like me. And Heidi. Created with the Gregor's Semi-Automatic LiveJournal Updater™. Update your journal today!
and i still have to finish catcher in the rye and read brave new world before monday. holy.shit.

I told my parents about Damian. It went well!


He might be coming down again for the weekend. God, I hope he does. And this time instead of spending hundreds on a hotel, he'll be able to sleep at my house. Said my parents. Am impressed with how well they took it, seeing as he's 20 and lives in Orlando and all.


<33333

i have a boyfriend. his name is damian,he's 20, and he lives in orlando. he visited all weekend, and i surprised him one final time this morning. surprised myself, too. it'll be hard, but i've got love and something to look forward to.

</3

i'm thinking of changing the background yet again, but won't bother at it so late at night. the fact that i think of 11:10 as so late at night is kind of sad--it's really not all so late. but i'm home,which is now something i'm getting used to. coming home early. instead of leaving wherever we were at 11:30 like we used to. but now that's when bridget gets home, and yes, i'll use her name here, even though i don't say it anywhere else. that girl. that's what i call her to you. to me, she's privately called other things, but you know that, although i never and won't ever, give you the satisfaction of saying what. and writing this is writing too much about you, and none of it is for you. out of sight, out of mind, right? well, not quite, actually.

anyways. my dad left for god knows where today to help with the hurricane. that's something he always does, being a cop--volunteer for whatever crises arises. wonder when he'll come back. soon,because it wasn't that bad, was it.

seriously considering majoring, yes majoring, in history with a specialization in european history. i'd love to travel europe and be a historian. not through just england and france, but countries like yugoslavia and russia and turkey. that'd be interesting. but what kind of a paying career could i honestly make out of that? something to think about.

need to go college touring this summer with my mother. maybe ill go back to orlando and visit disney again. well, universal or busch gardens this time, ive never been to busch gardens. sounds fun.

i don't feel well.

bought 2 bikinis today. buying more clothes tomorrow. sawgrass? broward today. 


you are my only one.


i am going to bust my ass this year in school.even though i did that last year, too.

His apparent partiality had subsided, his attentions were over, he was the admirer of someone else. Elizabeth was watchful enough to see it all, but she could see it and write of it without material pain. Her heart had been but slightly touched, and her vanity was satisfied with believing that she would have been his only choice, had fortune permitted it. The sudden acquisition of ten thousand pounds was the most remarkable charm of the young lady to whom he was now rendering himself agreeable; but Elizabeth, less clearsighted perhaps in his case than in Charlotte's, did not quarrel with him for his wish of independence. Nothing, on the contrary, could be more natural; and while able to suppose that it cost him a few struggles to relinquish her, she was ready to allow it a wise and desirable measure for both, and could very sincerely wish him happy. 
All this was acknowledged to Mrs.Gardiner; and after relating the circumstances, she thus went on: "I am now convinced, my dear aunt, that I have never been much in love; for had I really experienced that pure and elevating passion, I should at present detest his very name, and wish him all manner of evil. But my feelings are not only cordial towards him; they are even impartial towards Miss King. I cannot find out that I hate her at all, or that I am in the least unwilling to think her a very good sort of girl. There can be no love in all this. My watchfulness has been effectual; and though I should certainly be a more interesting object to all my acquaintance, were I distractedly in love with him, I cannot say that I regret my comparative insignificance. Importance may sometimes be purchased too dearly. Kitty and Lydia take his defection much more to heart than I do. They are young in the ways of the world, and not yet open to the mortifying conviction that handsome young men must have something to live on, as well as the plain."

--pride and prejudice
I guess I want him to be happy now. Even if happy is with her. Today is their one-month. Maybe I should send them a sweet e-card. Love, your ex-girlfriend. Haha, right.

i guess i've moved on more than you know. because i don't tell you everything, either.

right, greg?

just like the sophomore, joe. what we don't tell each other, it's quite amazing. 
but there's nothing to tell you since you wouldn't care anyways.



on another subject......
my dad, being the wonderful cop that he is, got my ticket ''taken care of''. =] so that's off my back. if they have our car done by the time my mom gets back from europe, maybe we won't even tell her...it could just be our little secret.
you know, that crash happened driving around his neighborhood. nobody seems to wonder about that--nobody has questioned me as to why i would possibly be doing that. 

i've just stayed at home for the past three days, but i'm going out tomorrow.
i'm looking forward to the plans we make. something excited i've never done before. like a whole new world i'll be introduced to. meeting and having new ''friends'' called names like triple c and ecstacy. 


and this is my journal,so if you read it you can't say a thing to me.
because....you don't care, so why would you anyway?






See. You think you can not care, and then there's that. 


I guess I'm excited. I guess I'm terrified. I guess I'm confused. I'm hurt, but I'm loving. I'm sad, but I'm ecstatic. It's everything one could ever be all bundled up into one big emotional mess that seems to function perfectly normal, and you'd never know because I'm so good now at not saying. We all know just how much I can act like what I'm really not, don't we? Like how I tried to pretend for so long that I was okay with you not being what I needed you to be, how I needed to pretend because I needed it to work. But this is a new kind of pretending now. Like I'm okay. And sometimes, its not pretending. That's when I'm busy, or talking. 

Maybe the most personal thing I've written in here in a long time. Its funny, quite heartbreaking actually, how this is the only way you know what and how I'm doing since you don't talk to me anymore. You still want to know me. You still want to care. You still do. 

But you're being a dick. 


Everyone should go and rent Closer, its the closest portrayal of the downsides of love there ever was. The hurt, the coldness, the backstabbing. Its all there.



Its all here.
